A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 1 of Chapter 24 of Title 33 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to general provisions regarding insurance, so as to prohibit insurers or third-party
3 administrators from conditioning the payment of any medical test or procedure or
4 prescription drug benefit on prior authorization; to amend Chapter 64 of Title 33 of the
5 Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to regulation and licensure of pharmacy benefit
6 managers, so as to prohibit pharmacy benefit managers from conditioning the payment of any
7 benefit for a prescription drug on prior authorization; to amend Article 2 of Chapter 34 of
8 Title 43 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to medical practice, so as to
9 provide that a physician shall not be required to obtain any prior authorization in their
10 exercise of patient healthcare; to amend Part 1 of Article 1 of Chapter 18 of Title 45 of the
11 Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to state employees' health insurance plan, so
12 as not to condition the payment of any medical test or procedure or prescription drug benefit
13 on prior authorization; to provide for definitions; to provide for related matters; to provide
14 for an effective date and applicability; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
