16 SECTION 1.
17 Article 1 of Chapter 24 of Title 33 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
18 general provisions regarding insurance, is amended by adding a new Code section to read as
19 follows:
20 "33-24-59.34.
21 (a) As used in this Code section, the term 'health benefit plan' means any individual or
22 group plan, policy, or contract for healthcare services issued, delivered, issued for delivery,
23 or renewed in this state which provides major medical benefits by a healthcare corporation,
24 health maintenance organization, preferred provider organization, accident and sickness
25 insurer, fraternal benefit society, hospital service corporation, medical service corporation,
26 or other insurer or similar entity.
27 (b) Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, neither an insurer nor a
28 third-party administrator shall condition the payment of any benefit for a medical test or
29 procedure or for a prescription drug upon any preapproval, prior authorization, or
30 precertification of any kind by an insurer if such test, procedure, or prescription drug is
31 otherwise covered under the health benefit plan and such medical test, procedure, or
32 prescription drug has been prescribed by licensed healthcare provider."
33 SECTION 2.
